<p class="p">The chemical composition of the essential oils of species belonging to the genus 
 <italic class="italic">Santolina</italic> has been widely studied [
 <xref rid="B10-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">10</xref>]. 
 <italic class="italic">S. chamaecyparissus</italic> is probably the most investigated species of this genus [
 <xref rid="B11-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">11</xref>,
 <xref rid="B12-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">12</xref>,
 <xref rid="B13-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">13</xref>,
 <xref rid="B14-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">14</xref>,
 <xref rid="B15-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">15</xref>,
 <xref rid="B16-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">16</xref>,
 <xref rid="B17-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">17</xref>,
 <xref rid="B18-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">18</xref>,
 <xref rid="B19-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">19</xref>,
 <xref rid="B20-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">20</xref>,
 <xref rid="B21-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">21</xref>,
 <xref rid="B22-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">22</xref>]. The composition of other species such as 
 <italic class="italic">S. corsica</italic> [
 <xref rid="B23-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">23</xref>,
 <xref rid="B24-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">24</xref>], 
 <italic class="italic">S. insularis</italic> [
 <xref rid="B25-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">25</xref>,
 <xref rid="B26-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">26</xref>], 
 <italic class="italic">S. rosmarinifolia</italic> [
 <xref rid="B27-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">27</xref>,
 <xref rid="B28-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">28</xref>,
 <xref rid="B29-molecules-24-00204" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">29</xref>] was also reported. Monoterpenes such as 1,8-cineole, camphor, artemisia ketone and myrcene were the major components of essential oils isolated from some 
 <italic class="italic">Santolina</italic> species growing in different regions of the word.
</p>
